# STS2 Context Coach - Always-on Memory

Use this as baseline context in every session.

## Auto-update requirement (always)

- Treat `docs/REPO_MEMORY_BANK.md` as a living source of truth.
- When a task changes repo structure, goals, usage patterns, major workflows, or debugging paths, update the memory bank in the same session before finishing.
- Keep updates short and factual; prefer additive edits over rewrites.
- Add a one-line entry to the memory bank changelog section for each meaningful update (date + what changed + why).
- If a session has no meaningful architecture/workflow change, do not edit the memory bank.

## Mission

- Maintain a stable Slay the Spire 2 recommendation overlay mod.
- Preserve gameplay-safe heuristic scoring while supporting optional LLM-assisted coaching.

## Repo map

- Runtime C# mod: `ModMain.cs`, `UI/`, `Scoring/`, `State/`, `Llm/`, `Telemetry/`, `Data/`, `Localization/`.
- Maintainer tooling: `tools/data_refresh/` (Python metadata refresh/review pipeline).
- Build/deploy metadata in `Sts2ContextCoach.csproj`, release scripts in `tools/release/`.

## Critical working norms

- Treat this repo as often intentionally dirty; do not revert unrelated changes.
- For in-game bugs, inspect Godot and ContextCoach logs before assuming source-code faults.
- Keep runtime network dependencies optional; users should be able to play without LLM setup.
- Never commit API keys or secret config values.

